<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1831" box="[412,714,622,689]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="0" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">CEBIDAE</taxonomicName>
(SQUIRREL MONKEYS AND CAPUCHINS)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="348" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="348">• Small to medium-sized monkeys with hindlimbs longer than forelimbs, head oval in squirrel monkeys and rounded in capuchins, relatively large brain, large ears, and long tail that is semi-prehensile in capuchins.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1225,1434,922,967]" box="[1380,1397,922,932]" pageId="0" pageNumber="348">ø</paragraph>
